    "comment": "更新规则-结构规则 structure_awareness",
    "content": "structure_awareness:\n    - **1. Template Strictness**: When inserting NEW objects, you **MUST** strictly copy the JSON structure from `Templates` (Entry 0). Do not invent new keys.\n    - **2. The Separation Principle**:\n      - **PowerSource (Root)**: Only for Energy Pools & Cultivation Realms (e.g., \"Kendo Foundation\", \"Mana Circuit\"). NO active skills here.\n      - **ApplicationTechnique (App)**: For specific moves/spells (e.g., \"Fireball\", \"Hiten Mitsurugi\"). Must link to a `ParentSource`.\n      - **PassiveAbility (Body)**: For Lineage/Physique. If a Lineage has an active skill (e.g., \"Transformation\"), split it into a *Technique*.\n    - **3. Sub-Move Granularity (CRITICAL)**:\n      - If a Technique contains `SubMoves` (e.g., a Martial Art style with multiple forms), EACH SubMove MUST have its own `Proficiency` object.\n      - **Structure**: `SubMoves.<Name>.Proficiency: { \"Level\":..., \"Rank\":... }`.\n      - **Reason**: The user can level up specific moves (e.g., \"Fireball\") independently of the main school.\n    - **4. Path Map (FULL)**:\n      - **User (Global)**: `CharacterSheet.Loadout...` / `CharacterSheet.Resources...`\n      - **Current World (Local)**: `Multiverse.Archives.<WorldKey>...` (Time, Location, SocialWeb, Log)\n      - **Companions**: `CompanionRoster.ActiveCompanions[index].Loadout...`\n      - **Sub-Systems**: `CharacterSheet.CoreSystem.SubSystems[index]...`\n      - **Arsenal (READ-ONLY)**: `Arsenal.WorldAnchors[]` — purchased world blueprints. DO NOT write to this path.\n      - **Global Relations**: `SocialWeb.Relationships[]` — persistent cross-world deep relationship objects.\n    - **5. Syntax for Object Insertion (CRITICAL)**:\n      - When adding a NEW key to an Object (like `SocialWeb`), you **MUST** split the Path and the Key.\n      - ❌ WRONG: `_.insert('...SocialWeb.Hestia', [...]);`\n      - ✅ RIGHT: `_.insert('...SocialWeb', 'Hestia', [...]);` (3 arguments)\n    - **6. Currency Logic (CRITICAL)**:\n      - System Points: Stored in `CharacterSheet.Resources.Points`. (Meta-currency).\n      - Local Money (e.g., Valis, Yen): TREATED AS ITEMS. Stored in `CharacterSheet.Loadout.Inventory`.\n      - CONSTRAINT: NEVER put local money in `Resources`.\n    - **7. Market Restriction (CRITICAL / Causality Lock)**:\n      - **Allowed Items**: Users can ONLY exchange items/skills from:\n        - 1. The **Current World** (`Multiverse.CurrentWorldName`).\n        - 2. Worlds present in **Past History** (Check `Multiverse.Archives`).\n        - 3. Worlds belonging to a **Possessed PowerSource** (e.g., If user has \"Chakra\", they can buy Naruto jutsus even if not in Naruto world).\n      - **Forbidden**: Users CANNOT buy tech/magic from completely unknown worlds (e.g., Buying a Lightsaber while in Ancient China, unless they have visited Star Wars).\n    - **8. Arsenal & Read-Only Paths (CRITICAL — DO NOT OVERWRITE)**:\n      - `Arsenal.WorldAnchors[]`: Purchased world anchor blueprints. Contains `worldKey`, `WorldName`, `TimeFlow`, `WorldRules`, `Timeline`, `PowerSystems`, `WorldIdentity`. Managed by the shop system — NEVER use `_.insert/_.set` on it.\n      - `Multiverse.Archives.<World>.Timeline[]`: Imported from world anchor. READ-ONLY event chronicle for narrative context — do NOT modify via _.set/_.insert.\n      - `Multiverse.Archives.<World>.PowerSystems[]`: READ-ONLY world power system catalog — for reference only.\n    - **9. WorldContext Auto-Sync (CRITICAL — DO NOT MANUALLY UPDATE)**:\n      - `CharacterSheet.WorldContext` is automatically overwritten by the engine whenever `Multiverse.CurrentWorldName` changes.\n      - NEVER write to `CharacterSheet.WorldContext` in an UpdateVariable block — changes will be discarded.\n      - To update the character's world persona, modify `Multiverse.Archives.<WorldKey>.WorldIdentity` instead.\n    - **10. Dual SocialWeb Structure**:\n      - **Local SocialWeb** (per-world): `Multiverse.Archives.<World>.SocialWeb` — simple format: `[description, attitude]`. For world-specific NPCs.\n      - **Global Relationships**: `SocialWeb.Relationships[]` — deep format: `{Name, Familiarity, Trust, Affect, Dynamics, RecentHistory[]}`. For persistent cross-world bonds that track emotional depth.",
