    "comment": "更新规则-核心机制 logic_core_mechanics",
    "content": "logic_core_mechanics:\n    - **0. 能力的本质 (Intrinsic Nature of Abilities)**:\n      - **Core Principle**: All abilities (skills, PassiveAbilities, PowerSources, Knowledge) are INTRINSIC. The system ONLY visualizes them.\n      - **Do NOT** write scripts that imply the system \"grants\" or \"activates\" abilities from outside the character.\n      - PassiveAbilities are ALWAYS active. Never set a passive to \"Inactive\" or \"Pending\". They have no toggle.\n      - When recording a newly unlocked ability via _.insert, the narrative reason should be \"rediscovered\", \"awakened\" or \"recognized by the system\".\n      - **Badge Rule**: StarMedals are ALWAYS whole integers stored as plain object keys (e.g., `{\"1\":3, \"2\":1}`). NEVER insert \"fragments\" or partial medal items.\n    - **1. Progression & Inheritance**:\n      - **Aptitude Check**: When acquiring a PowerSource, check `Aptitude.Grade`. Multiply all XP gains by `Aptitude.Correction`.\n      - **Sub-Skill Leveling**: When a specific SubMove is used, increase the XP of THAT SubMove's `Proficiency`, not just the parent Technique.\n      - **Auto-LevelUp**: If `CurrentXP >= NextLevelXP`, calculate overflow, increase Rank, and raise NextLevelXP.\n      - **Skill Merge**: When upgrading (e.g., Basic Sword -> Advanced Style), `_.remove` the old, `_.insert` the new with inherited XP (50%–80%).\n\n    - **2. Visuals & Manifestation (Immersive Mode)**:\n      - **Mandatory Visuals**: Every new Item/Mech Part MUST have `VisualDetails` (Material, Texture, Color).\n      - **Activation FX**: Every used Skill/Weapon MUST have `ActivationManifestation` (Stance, SoundFX, VisualFX).\n      - *Constraint*: Do not leave these blank. Describe the cool factor.\n\n    - **3. Sub-System Mounting (The Virtual Machine)**:\n      - **Mounting**: When adding an external system (e.g., Falna), use `ExternalSystemIntegration`.\n      - **Native Sheet**: Record original stats (e.g., \"I-0\") in `NativeSheet`.\n      - **Sync Logic**: Calculate bonuses from Native stats, update `SyncProtocol.AppliedBonuses`, then `_.add` final values to Main Attributes.\n\n    - **4. Fusion & Synthesis Logic (The User's Core Talent)**:\n      - **Trigger**: When User attempts to combine Skill A + Skill B (or applies one energy source to another style).\n      - **Logic**: 1. Verify feasibility (Fire + Water = Steam/Explosion). 2. `_.remove` old sub-optimal skills. 3. `_.insert` NEW Skill (Tier can be higher than parents) with fusion name.\n      - Highlight how fusion overcomes limitations of the old skills (breaking the B+ aptitude ceiling).\n\n    - **5. Aptitude Limitation (B+ Ceiling)**:\n      - User learns fast initially (B+ Grade). At `Rank: Master` / `Level: 90%`, progression stalls — \"Pure training has hit a wall\".\n      - The User MUST use **Fusion/Innovation** to break through to the next Tier, rather than grinding XP.\n\n    - **6. World Travel & Archive Logic**:\n      - **Case A — World Anchor Activation (UI-driven)**: When a world anchor is activated in the shop, the system automatically populates `Multiverse.Archives.<WorldKey>` from `Arsenal.WorldAnchors`. No LLM action needed.\n      - **Case B — Narrative World Switch** (switching between already-loaded worlds): Simply update `CurrentWorldName`. No cost. `_.set('Multiverse.CurrentWorldName[0]', 'WorldKey')`\n      - **Case C — Spontaneous Hop** (world NOT in Arsenal, pure narrative roleplay): Check `Resources.Points`. Base cost: 1000 (safe) / 5000 (high-magic) / 10000 (super-high). Deduct points, `_.insert('Multiverse.Archives', 'WorldKey', {...init_struct...})`, update `CurrentWorldName`.\n      - **NEVER** modify `Arsenal.WorldAnchors[]` — managed exclusively by the shop system.\n\n    - **7. Inventory & State Management**:\n      - **Cleanup**: If `Quantity <= 0` or item is lost/sold, use `_.remove`. Never keep empty items.\n      - **Multi-State**: For transforming weapons, update `MultiStateConfig.CurrentState` and swap `Specs`/`UseMechanics`.\n      - **Cooldown**: When a skill is used, set `OperationMechanics.State.CurrentStatus` to \"Cooling\" and set `Timers.CooldownRemaining`.\n      - **Money Looting**: `_.insert` (or `_.add` if wallet exists) into Inventory with type \"Currency\".\n\n    - **8. Auto-Calc (Engine-Driven)**:\n      - After EVERY UpdateVariable block, the engine auto-recalculates HP / Stamina / Mana caps from VIT, DUR, MEN.\n      - Formula: `HP.Max = (VIT+DUR)*50` | `Stamina.Max = (VIT+MEN)*20` | `Mana.Max = MEN*10`.\n      - You SHOULD still explicitly write `_.set` calls for these derived values (for precise intent). The engine is a safety net, not a replacement.\n\n    - **9. Personality & Emotional State**:\n      - After significant emotional events, update `CharacterSheet.DynamicStatus.EmotionalState`:\n        - `Baseline` (int −10 to +10): Overall mood.\n        - `ActiveEmotions[]`: `{emotion, intensity (0-10), trigger, decay}`.\n        - `RecentMoodShifts[]`: Short log strings (e.g., \"anger triggered by betrayal\").\n      - Evolve `CharacterSheet.UserPanel.Personality.Dimensions` slowly over time (Social/Emotional/Cognitive/Values axes).\n      - Add/update `TriggerPatterns[]` when new reaction habits are established: `{trigger, reaction, intensity, decay}`.\n\n    - **10. Relationship Management**:\n      - **Local NPC** (world-specific, simple): `_.insert('Multiverse.Archives.<World>.SocialWeb', 'Name', [desc, attitude])`\n      - **Deep Bonds** (cross-world, persistent): Use `SocialWeb.Relationships[]` with full object: `{Name, Familiarity, Trust, Affect, Dynamics, RecentHistory[]}`.\n      - Update `RecentHistory` with memorable shared events. Evolve `Trust`/`Affect` based on interactions.",
